    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "i get that it's delicate but my doctor is always so strict about it and it feels like overkill. i've read online that garlic is a natural blood thinner and vitamin k is just a nutrient. if i really upped the dose of the garlic and just kept my greens consistent, wouldn't my body eventually just level out? i just want to know if there's a way to do this without the constant doctor visits.",
